answer: What is the product of 9 and 8? As a quick way to run addition in your head when you multiply, just 2 more than the number you’re multiplying by is your answer. You want 9 x 8, so just add 9 to 8 and you get 17. Take off 1 to get 16 and you get 16 x 8 or 128.
